message.content:
A 'Thamnophis atratus' is a species of snake.
It is commonly referred to as the western aquatic garter snake.
It has a distinct black and white striped pattern.
The scales of its body are smooth and glossy.
It has a slender, cylindrical body with a flattened head.
This snake can be found in water bodies such as rivers, ponds and lakes.
It is a non-venomous snake species.
